    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-24T10:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-24T10:48:00-05:00" n="345"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d345">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.1511/108: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul in Charge of the Legation in Honduras</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lawton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-24T10:00:00-05:48">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1919, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received October 25, 11.50 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>… The President also asked me if possible to secure from the Department an
                    expression of the attitude of the Department towards his administration and
                    approval of official acts to date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lawton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
